            <physDesc>
               <p>No day in the Gregorian calendar corresponds to the date in this colophon. Since the scribe is the same who wrote SUB 35-3028 (completed on 15 January 1803), we assume that the day of the week recorded in this date (Monday) is wrong: by correcting it into Sunday, the date corresponds to 19 December 1802, that is around one month before the date in SUB 35-3028. (2) In the translation we understand saṃpūrṇaṃ to be an independent sentence, but it is seems more plausible that the syntax of the whole sentence is incorrect, with a failed attempt at a passive construction. The combination of a Tamil instrumental and the verbal form eḻutiṉatu cannot in fact be found anywhere else.</p>
            </physDesc>
