         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            
               <lg><l>The loss of letters that was made dense in this manuscript, or a slip of the pencil written in the unceasing [writing].</l>
              <l> May the good ones forgive the mistake made by the hand concerning the heap of letters that is made (kṛtau > kṛte ?) either loose or dense.</l>
               <l>What is a dropped character (akṣara) or word, as well as the deficiency of a mora, may all that be forgiven, o god Nārāyaṇa, honour to you.</l>
               <l>Words, lines, syllables with visargas, nasal signs, morae:  may the Supreme Being forgive whether there are too few or too many.</l></lg>
            
            <p>Year Dundubhi, month of Dhanur, 7th day, Monday: in this auspicious day the illustrious Rāmāyaṇasārasaṃkṣepa was copied (eḻutiṉatu [sic!]) by Kiṭāmpi Śrīkṛṣṇadāsaṉ; it is completed.</p> 
